cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper proposes a self-supervised approach for learning representations and robotic behaviors entirely from unlabeled videos, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of metric learning loss and reinforcement learning algorithms also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of videos as the primary data source suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
